11-25|title=Country Albums chart for November 25, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|December 2}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-12-02|title=Country Albums chart for December 2, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|December 9}}\n|rowspan=\"4\"| ''[[Fresh Horses (album)|Fresh Horses]]'' \n|rowspan=\"4\"| {{sortname|Garth|Brooks}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-12-09|title=Country Albums chart for December 9, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|December 16}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-12-16|title=Country Albums chart for December 16, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|December 23}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-12-23|title=Country Albums chart for December 23, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|December 30}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-12-30|title=Country Albums chart for December 30, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{US Country Albums}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of number-one country albums in the United States|1995]]\n[[Category:1995 record charts]]\n", "text_old": "[[File:JMM1862004-06-18.jpg|thumb|right|250px|alt=Singer John Michael Montogmery|[[John Michael Montgomery]] spent 13 consecutive weeks at number one with [[John Michael Montgomery (album)|his eponymous album]].]] \n[[Top Country Albums]] is a [[record chart|chart]] that ranks the top-performing [[country music]] albums in the United States, published by ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]''.  In 1995, seven different albums topped the chart, based on sales reports submitted by a representative sample of stores nationwide.<ref>{{cite book|title=Joel Whitburn Presents Hot Country Albums: Billboard 1964 to 2007|first=Joel|last=Whitburn|publisher=Record Research, Incorporated|date=2008|isbn=9780898201734|page=6}}</ref>\n\nIn the issue of ''Billboard'' dated January 7, [[Garth Brooks]] was at number one with the compilation album ''[[The Hits (Garth Brooks album)|The Hits]]'', its second week in the top spot.<ref name=J7 />  The album held the peak position for the first 14 weeks of 1995 and returned to number one for a single week later in the year; its 16 weeks atop the chart took Brooks's total number of weeks in the top spot to 113 in less than five years.<ref>{{cite book|title=Joel Whitburn Presents Hot Country Albums: Billboard 1964 to 2007|first=Joel|last=Whitburn|publisher=Record Research, Incorporated|date=2008|isbn=9780898201734|page=40}}</ref>  The singer returned to number one in December with his next album ''[[Fresh Horses (album)|Fresh Horses]]'', which held the top spot for the final four weeks of the year; he was the only artist to achieve more than one chart-topper during 1995.  ''The Hits'' was the only one of 1995's Top Country Albums number ones to also top the all-genre ''[[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]] chart.\n\nIn July, [[Shania Twain]] gained her first number one with ''[[The Woman in Me (Shania Twain album)|The Woman in Me]]''; the album spent 11 weeks in the top spot in 1995 but would return to number one for a further 18 weeks the following year, making it the longest-running number one country album to date by a female artist.<ref>{{cite book|title=Joel Whitburn Presents Hot Country Albums: Billboard 1964 to 2007|first=Joel|last=Whitburn|publisher=Record Research, Incorporated|date=2008|isbn=9780898201734|page=256}}</ref>  The album launched the Canadian singer to stardom in both the country and pop markets, and helped to make her one of the most successful recording artists of the 1990s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allmusic.com/artist/shania-twain-mn0000161808/biography|title=Shania Twain Biography & History|first=Stephen Thomas|last=Erlewin|publisher=[[AllMusic]]|accessdate=April 24, 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Chart history==\n[[File:Garth Brooks at We Are One (edit).jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Garth Brooks|[[Garth Brooks]] both began and ended the year at number one.]]\n[[File:ShaniaTwain1.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Shania Twain|[[Shania Twain]] reached number one for the first time with ''[[The Woman in Me (Shania Twain album)|The Woman in Me]]''.]]\n[[File:Alan Jackson (3023584051).jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Alan Jackson|[[Alan Jackson]] topped the chart with ''[[The Greatest Hits Collection (Alan Jackson album)|The Greatest Hits Collection]]''.]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!scope=col|Issue date\n!scope=col|Title\n!scope=col|Artist(s)\n!scope=col class=unsortable|Ref.\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 7}}\n|rowspan=\"14\"|''{{sort|Hits|[[The Hits (Garth Brooks album)|The Hits]]}}''\n|rowspan=\"14\"| {{sortname|Garth|Brooks}}\n|align=center|<ref name=J7>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-01-07|title=Country Albums chart for January 7, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 14}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-01-14|title=Country Albums chart for January 14, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 21}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-01-21|title=Country Albums chart for January 21, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 28}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-01-28|title=Country Albums chart for January 28, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|February 4}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-02-04|title=Country Albums chart for February 4, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|February 11}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-02-11|title=Country Albums chart for February 11, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|February 18}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-02-18|title=Country Albums chart for February 18, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|February 25}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-02-25|title=Country Albums chart for February 25, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|March 4}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-03-04|title=Country Albums chart for March 4, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|March 11}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-03-11|title=Country Albums chart for March 11, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|March 18}}\n|align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/country-albums/1995-03-18|title=Country Albums chart for March 18, 1995|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|March 25}